  'angkor-wat' => [
    'name' => 'Angkor Wat Yatra',
    'months' => 'February, December',
    'duration' => '8 Days',
    'icon' => 'fa-globe-asia',
    'short_desc' => 'Journey to the magnificent Angkor Wat temple complex in Cambodia — a sacred heritage pilgrimage.',
    'banner_image' => '../assets/images/banners/angkor-wat.jpg',
    'content_image' => null,
    'description_paragraphs' => [
      'Angkor Wat is an architectural masterpiece and the largest religious monument in the world – covering an area four times the size of Vatican City. It was built by the Khmer King Suryavarman II in the first half of the 12th century, around the year 1110-1150, making Angkor Wat almost 900 years old.',
      'The temple complex, built in the capital of the Khmer Empire, took approximately 30 years to build. It was originally dedicated to the Hindu god Vishnu before becoming a Buddhist temple by the end of the 12th century.',
      'One of the first Western visitors to the temple was Antonio de Madalena, a Portuguese friar who visited in 1586. Angkor Wat was then effectively rediscovered by the French explorer Henri Mouhot in the 1840s. Mouhot described Angkor Wat as grander than anything left to us by Greece or Rome and spread the word about this incredible monument to the western world.',
      'The French, who ruled Cambodia for much of the 20th century, restored the site in the early 1900s for tourism purposes. However, this work was then disrupted by the Cambodian Civil War and during the rule of the Khmer Rouge. Angkor Wat sustained minimal damage – however there are still bullet holes on its outer walls due to the battles of the Khmer Rouge regime.',
      'Cambodia gained independence from France in 1953 and has controlled Angkor Wat ever since.',
      'In 1992 the temple complex was named a UNESCO World Heritage site, and is now a highly popular tourist attraction in Cambodia - welcoming 2 million visitors every year. The most popular time to visit Angkor Wat is in the early hours of the morning; to witness a beautiful sunrise over the magical temple.',
    ],
    'places' => [
      ['name' => 'Angkor Wat Temple', 'description' => 'The main temple complex, the largest religious monument in the world. Originally dedicated to Lord Vishnu, it features stunning bas-reliefs and iconic lotus-shaped towers.'],
      ['name' => 'Wat Arun', 'description' => 'The majestic Temple of Dawn, featuring a grand central prang decorated with colorful porcelain.'],
      ['name' => 'Golden Buddha', 'description' => 'A famous temple housing a massive solid gold statue of Buddha, showcasing ancient craftsmanship.'],
      ['name' => 'Diamond Shop', 'description' => 'Explore the local gem industry and beautiful collections of precious stones.'],
      ['name' => 'Golden Mount Temple', 'description' => 'A historic temple on a hill offering panoramic views of the city, featuring a sacred golden chedi.'],
      ['name' => 'Sleeping Buddha', 'description' => 'Reverent temple housing a giant reclining statue of Buddha, representing entry into Nirvana.'],
      ['name' => 'Royal Palace', 'description' => 'A spectacular complex of buildings which serves as the official royal residence of the King of Cambodia.'],
      ['name' => 'Hanuman Dance Show', 'description' => 'A traditional cultural dance performance depicting the pastimes of Lord Hanuman from the Ramayana.'],
      ['name' => 'Brahma Ganesh Temple', 'description' => 'A sacred shrine dedicated to Lord Brahma and Lord Ganesha, reflecting Hindu-Khmer heritage.'],
      ['name' => 'Bayon Brahma', 'description' => 'The temple at the center of Angkor Thom, known for its unique stone towers carved with massive serene faces.'],
      ['name' => 'Ta Prohm Banyan Forest', 'description' => 'The famous temple left in much the same condition as it was found, with giant banyan and silk-cotton tree roots wrapping around the stone walls.'],
      ['name' => 'Kulen Mountain & Water Falls', 'description' => 'A holy mountain range featuring beautiful waterfalls and the birthplace of the ancient Khmer Empire.'],
      ['name' => 'Sahasralinga Temple', 'description' => 'A sacred riverbed featuring hundreds of carvings of Shiva Lingas carved directly into the rocks under the water.'],
    ],
    'highlights' => ['Angkor Wat Temple Complex', 'Sahasralinga Temple', 'Ta Prohm Banyan Forest', 'Hanuman Dance Show', 'Kulen Mountain & Water Falls'],
